WEBVTT

00:03.090 --> 00:06.310
[ Sighs ] You let a wanted felon
waltz back into your life

00:06.354 --> 00:08.443
and steal your kids.

00:08.486 --> 00:10.053
How could you
let him do that?

00:11.402 --> 00:12.664
I --

00:12.708 --> 00:14.231
You are terrible parents.

00:14.275 --> 00:15.885
We've been told that
a few times.

00:15.928 --> 00:18.888
Children are
your life's blood.

00:18.931 --> 00:20.368
They are so precious.

00:20.411 --> 00:22.544
I mean, I'm sure they were
when they were younger.

00:22.587 --> 00:24.894
Yeah, well, the daughter is
a bit on the spectrum.

00:24.937 --> 00:26.635
And their son, I don't know
how he functions in life.

00:26.678 --> 00:27.897
I mean, you should
have seen him.

00:27.940 --> 00:29.768
He was getting
this handy from...

00:29.812 --> 00:31.074
-Whoa, whoa.
-What?

00:31.118 --> 00:32.902
Hey.
How do you know that?

00:32.945 --> 00:34.425
Were you spying on us?

00:34.469 --> 00:36.471
In our home?

00:37.428 --> 00:39.430
Don't doodle.
Answer the question.

00:39.474 --> 00:42.259
Did you put a camera
in our house?

00:46.655 --> 00:49.179
-Kids?
-What, are they sleeping?

00:49.223 --> 00:51.877
-It's 9:30. No.
-Hey, kids. Come on out here.

00:51.921 --> 00:53.966
We've got some stuff
to talk to you about.

00:54.750 --> 00:57.100
Guys? Super D?

00:57.144 --> 00:59.015
Jared?

00:59.059 --> 01:01.974
We've got some news.
It's not great.

01:02.018 --> 01:04.064
Hey.

01:06.109 --> 01:07.676
Kids?

01:12.985 --> 01:14.770
I can't find them.

01:14.813 --> 01:17.294
-Maybe they're down at Chase's?
-Probably. I'll go get them.

01:28.262 --> 01:31.265
[ Sighs ]

01:32.353 --> 01:34.877
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

01:36.705 --> 01:39.751
♪♪

01:50.936 --> 01:52.938
What the hell?

02:13.785 --> 02:15.091
What the...

02:15.135 --> 02:17.137
Holy shit.

02:18.442 --> 02:20.879
What's in that?

02:29.975 --> 02:31.412
Oh, geez!

02:31.455 --> 02:34.502
♪♪

02:59.831 --> 03:01.268
What the shit?

03:02.747 --> 03:05.315
♪ Somewhere behind the skyline

03:05.359 --> 03:07.883
♪ There is a place
I'm thinkin' ♪

03:07.926 --> 03:11.147
[ Distorted music plays ]

03:14.019 --> 03:16.152
What are you do...
What? What?
[ Mouthing ]

03:16.196 --> 03:18.285
Say words with your mouth.
Use noise.

03:22.767 --> 03:24.900
Bags?

03:24.943 --> 03:26.467
Oh, bugs?

03:26.510 --> 03:28.382
That's what this --
You don't do this!

03:28.425 --> 03:29.905
You call an exterminator.

03:29.948 --> 03:31.385
What is your problem?

03:33.604 --> 03:37.086
Nate, pour children
are not at the Lewises'.

03:37.129 --> 03:39.349
Go faster, go faster, go faster.
Come on.

03:39.393 --> 03:40.611
Why -- I --

03:40.655 --> 03:42.265
Just show it to me.

03:42.309 --> 03:44.789
Hurry.

03:44.833 --> 03:46.095
People are liste--
People are listening?

03:46.138 --> 03:47.488
Yes,
the walls are paper thin.

03:47.531 --> 03:48.880
We've established this.
What are you doing.

03:48.924 --> 03:51.579
Baby, what are you doing?
Stop doing that.

03:51.622 --> 03:53.276
Stop eating that.
-[ Speaks indistinctly ]

03:53.320 --> 03:55.060
-What? What?
-[ Coughs ]

03:55.104 --> 03:57.454
[ Gasps ]
It's too thick.

03:57.498 --> 03:59.543
It's the evidence.

04:02.459 --> 04:03.721
[ Whispering ]
See the camera?

04:03.765 --> 04:05.375
Oh, shit. He was right.

04:05.419 --> 04:07.203
-Who was right?
-Oh, my dad.

04:07.247 --> 04:09.249
I hate it when he's right.Who?
What are you talking about?

04:09.292 --> 04:10.641
-My father.
-What about him?

04:10.685 --> 04:12.861
-The mail police!
-That makes less sense!

04:12.904 --> 04:14.428
-Help me with this.
-What?

04:14.471 --> 04:16.386
-Help me get this off.
-Oh, bugs in the mattress?

04:16.430 --> 04:17.387
Yep. Yep.

04:17.431 --> 04:19.259
Get off.

04:21.304 --> 04:23.306
Nate: Bugs.

04:25.352 --> 04:27.179
What?

04:27.223 --> 04:29.225
Why would you
put that in there?

04:29.269 --> 04:30.574
God.

04:30.618 --> 04:32.184
[ Grunts ]

04:32.228 --> 04:34.317
No wonder I was getting
such a shitty night's sleep.

04:35.840 --> 04:37.059
Ah.

04:37.102 --> 04:38.539
What are you doing?
Oh, my God.

04:38.582 --> 04:40.018
-It's not what it looks like.
-It looks like

04:40.062 --> 04:41.846
you're thumbing around
in a bowl of human feces.

04:41.890 --> 04:43.239
Which, that wasn't me,
by the way.

04:43.283 --> 04:44.414
The kids must have --

04:44.458 --> 04:46.677
Oh my God!
Why would you do that?

04:46.721 --> 04:48.113
It's all a part
of his escape plan.

04:48.157 --> 04:49.941
-What kind of plan is that?
-Relax.

04:49.985 --> 04:51.639
It's a candy bar
and chocolate sauce,

04:51.682 --> 04:52.901
so nobody
looks in the toilet.

04:52.944 --> 04:54.424
It's still
disgusting looking.

04:54.990 --> 04:55.947
What is that?
-Here.

04:55.991 --> 04:57.993
Oh! Oh, my God.

04:58.036 --> 04:59.647
-Open it.
-Wha-- No!

04:59.690 --> 05:02.650
-It's chocolate sauce!
-It was still in toilet water!

05:04.869 --> 05:07.132
What is this, airline tickets?
What, did he buy us a trip?

05:07.176 --> 05:08.177
-No.
-That's nice.

05:08.220 --> 05:09.657
And what are these numbers?

05:09.700 --> 05:11.049
-They're coordinates.
-For what?

05:11.093 --> 05:12.529
Who gives us
coordinates?

05:12.573 --> 05:15.576
-He took our children.
-He didn't take our --

05:15.619 --> 05:16.925
Why would he
take our children?

05:16.968 --> 05:19.536
He took our children
in exchange for that.

05:19.580 --> 05:22.626
♪♪

05:26.543 --> 05:29.764
Say goodbye to a formerly
great country, kids.

05:29.807 --> 05:32.462
Yeah.
This is kind of weird, you know?

05:32.506 --> 05:34.812
Not really.
I've watched overregulation

05:34.856 --> 05:37.554
cripple this country
since the Carter administration.

05:37.598 --> 05:40.122
No. I mean,
are we being kidnapped?

05:40.165 --> 05:41.428
I don't think so.

05:41.471 --> 05:42.820
You came willingly.

05:42.864 --> 05:44.387
You said our parents
were gonna be here.

05:44.431 --> 05:46.781
No. I said your parents
would meet you there.

05:49.740 --> 05:52.700
Don't worry.
They're on their way.

05:54.919 --> 05:56.399
I know I left the keys
in here somewhere.

05:56.443 --> 05:57.574
Why don't we just fly?

05:57.618 --> 05:58.923
Because I'm on
the no-fly list.

05:58.967 --> 06:00.185
How do you get
on that list, anyway?

06:00.229 --> 06:01.970
-I'll tell you later.
-That's...

06:02.013 --> 06:04.407
Look, I didn't get
a chance to straighten up,

06:04.451 --> 06:05.582
but she's a good van.

06:05.626 --> 06:07.497
Thank you for
doing this, again.

06:07.541 --> 06:09.978
And the speedometer,
odometer, and tachometer,

06:10.021 --> 06:11.327
they're all
a little finicky.

06:11.371 --> 06:13.198
You know, most of
it's just there for show.

06:13.242 --> 06:14.504
Sure. As long as the gas gauge
works, that's all that matters.

06:14.548 --> 06:16.332
Not since the mid '90s.

06:16.376 --> 06:18.421
So I wouldn't push it more than
two hours before a refill.

06:18.465 --> 06:21.337
[ Keys jingle ]
-Aha! Got 'em!

06:21.381 --> 06:23.687
Great. That's --
You're a lifesaver, pal.

06:23.731 --> 06:25.907
Listen to me, okay?
We're New Yorkers.

06:25.950 --> 06:28.213
When the chips are down,
we're there for each other.

06:28.257 --> 06:30.651
We're resilient
in the face of adversity.

06:30.694 --> 06:32.435
Although some people say
we're a little rude,

06:32.479 --> 06:33.784
we're a little
quick to anger --

06:33.828 --> 06:35.395
I'm so sorry.
We really don't have time

06:35.438 --> 06:36.874
for this whole New York
is the best bullshit.

06:36.918 --> 06:38.702
Sorry.
-Exactly. Screw politeness.

06:38.746 --> 06:40.356
Get right to the point.

06:40.400 --> 06:43.620
But underneath all that bluster,
we're in it together.

06:44.926 --> 06:46.318
So how long
you need it for?

06:46.362 --> 06:48.799
A week?
10 days tops.

06:48.843 --> 06:51.367
Ooh, slight problem.

06:51.411 --> 06:54.283
Sometimes when I'm in between
places, I sleep in my vehicle.

06:54.326 --> 06:56.328
Like, for the last
couple of years.

06:56.372 --> 06:58.548
Okay. Well -- Well, why don't
you just stay at our place?

06:58.592 --> 07:00.202
What?
The rent's paid through
the end of the month

07:00.245 --> 07:02.160
and then after that, I don't
know what we're gonna do.

07:02.204 --> 07:03.466
-Okay.
-Yeah, great. Thank you.

07:03.510 --> 07:04.902
-Thanks again, man.
-Great, yeah.

07:04.946 --> 07:06.382
-Thank you so much.
-Great. Need any help?

07:06.426 --> 07:07.731
-No, I got it.
-All right. I should drive.

07:07.775 --> 07:09.820
Yeah.

07:09.864 --> 07:13.041
Okay. Let's go.
-Take care, man.

07:13.084 --> 07:14.216
-All right.
-This is it, huh?

07:14.259 --> 07:15.739
-Yep.
-Come here, come here.

07:15.783 --> 07:17.524
I'm not a hugger.
Okay.

07:17.567 --> 07:18.786
Bring those kids
home safe, huh?

07:18.829 --> 07:20.352
-Yep.
-Hurry up, Nate. Come on.

07:20.396 --> 07:21.484
He's kissing me.

07:21.528 --> 07:23.965
We just heard the news.

07:24.008 --> 07:26.141
Just awful.
-You'll be in our thoughts

07:26.184 --> 07:27.838
and non-denominational
meditations tonight.

07:27.882 --> 07:29.274
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

07:29.318 --> 07:30.624
Oh, and we brought you
some homemade caramel corn

07:30.667 --> 07:32.060
for the trip.
-Okay, great.

07:32.103 --> 07:33.714
We really have to go.
Thank you so much.

07:33.757 --> 07:35.977
All families go through this.
Or something like it.

07:36.020 --> 07:38.240
Our little family's
going through its own tragedy.

07:38.283 --> 07:39.894
We're very sorry,
but we really have to go.

07:39.937 --> 07:41.156
I found a lump.

07:41.199 --> 07:42.636
-That's --
-She had a few removed

07:42.679 --> 07:44.507
a few years ago,
but this --

07:44.551 --> 07:45.900
This one's
not looking good.

07:45.943 --> 07:48.293
-It's spreading.
-I thought we had it beat,

07:48.337 --> 07:51.079
but it's looking like it's gonna
be terminal this time.

07:51.122 --> 07:52.515
Nate, we have to go.
We have to go right now, please.

07:52.559 --> 07:54.822
-She has cancer.
-We don't know her very well.

07:54.865 --> 07:56.301
Just have some sympathy.

07:56.345 --> 07:58.652
-She's only 25.
-Oh, come on.

07:58.695 --> 08:00.044
You're pushing
this age thing way too far.

08:00.088 --> 08:02.133
Okay, hold on.
Who's 25?

08:02.177 --> 08:04.396
-Our cat.
-Oh [bleep] off.

08:06.007 --> 08:07.791
She's not really
a cat person.

08:07.835 --> 08:10.228
You understand.
Our kids were kidnappped.

08:10.272 --> 08:12.927
But she's got lumps.
Everywhere.

08:12.970 --> 08:16.060
I don't really give
a shit, either.

08:16.104 --> 08:18.193
[ Cries ]

08:19.455 --> 08:21.501
Thanks for these!

08:26.636 --> 08:29.552
♪♪

08:39.649 --> 08:41.085
♪ La, la, la-la

08:41.129 --> 08:45.655
♪ La, la, la-la, la-la, la

08:45.699 --> 08:48.005
You know it took us six days
to drive to Florida last time.

08:48.049 --> 08:49.529
That's why we're not
stopping this time.

08:49.572 --> 08:51.922
Gave us first-class tickets.
That's pretty generous.

08:51.966 --> 08:53.663
Can I remind you that
he kidnapped our children

08:53.707 --> 08:55.143
for a piece of metal?

08:55.186 --> 08:57.101
So maybe let's have
a little perspective.

08:57.145 --> 08:59.060
Is it really kidnapping
if he's their grandfather?

08:59.103 --> 09:00.670
Yeah.
Yeah, it is, actually.

09:00.714 --> 09:02.324
Don't fall
for his bullshit, Nate.

09:02.367 --> 09:04.587
My opinion of my dad
is our opinion. Got it?

09:04.631 --> 09:08.548
I got it, got it.
Just...

09:08.591 --> 09:10.245
First-class seats.
-God.

09:10.288 --> 09:12.464
I've never flown
first class before.

09:12.508 --> 09:13.988
I hear it's really great.

09:14.031 --> 09:15.642
-It's fine.
-Nah, it's better than fine.

09:15.685 --> 09:18.775
You know, back when I was
flying economy, middle seats,

09:18.819 --> 09:20.298
all those business trips
for PFR.

09:20.342 --> 09:23.432
I'd walk past those guys
that get to go on first.

09:23.475 --> 09:25.477
And then they're sitting there
with their hot nuts

09:25.521 --> 09:29.525
and free newspapers,
drinking mimosas.

09:29.569 --> 09:31.353
Lie-flat beds.

09:31.396 --> 09:33.747
Of course I wouldn't use that.
I'd be too excited to sleep.

09:33.790 --> 09:35.183
[ Chuckles ]

09:35.226 --> 09:37.054
I was like, "One day.

09:37.098 --> 09:40.144
One day, I'm gonna be up
in front of that curtain."

09:41.450 --> 09:43.670
And here it is.

09:43.713 --> 09:45.585
And we get to use it.

09:45.628 --> 09:47.021
They give you socks.

09:47.064 --> 09:49.893
Socks.
That's so great.

09:49.937 --> 09:52.766
-You have socks.
-I know, but not plane socks.

09:52.809 --> 09:55.638
That's something special.

09:55.682 --> 09:56.900
Is it?

09:56.944 --> 09:59.250
They've never touched
the ground.

09:59.294 --> 10:00.861
Literally.

10:00.904 --> 10:03.211
You kids want anything?

10:03.254 --> 10:05.648
Pilot can play the violin
if you want.

10:05.692 --> 10:08.825
Or she can
give you a massage.

10:10.479 --> 10:13.047
I think I should do
some pushups first.

10:13.090 --> 10:14.570
What should we call you?

10:14.614 --> 10:18.313
Whatever you want to call me.
J.R. is fine.

10:18.356 --> 10:19.706
But you're
our grandfather.

10:19.749 --> 10:21.882
We can't call you
by your actual name.

10:21.925 --> 10:25.755
That's a bit traditional,
but okay, sure.

10:25.799 --> 10:26.756
What do you got?

10:26.800 --> 10:28.410
What about just "grandpa"?

10:28.453 --> 10:31.108
Mm, that makes me
feel kind of old.

10:31.152 --> 10:32.806
-Baba?
-That's a bottle.

10:32.849 --> 10:35.156
-Grandfather?
-Too formal, no?

10:35.199 --> 10:37.332
-Bobo.
-What am I, a clown?

10:37.375 --> 10:39.464
-G Daddy.
-That's too urban.

10:39.508 --> 10:41.031
-Grampy.
-Too rural.

10:41.075 --> 10:44.121
-What about just Gramps?
-Let's get away from the Gs.

10:44.165 --> 10:45.775
You know what...

10:45.819 --> 10:47.168
What about PP?

10:47.211 --> 10:48.735
What the hell
does that even mean?

10:48.778 --> 10:50.301
-Zaide?
-Come on.

10:50.345 --> 10:52.521
If you're not gonna take
any of this seriously --

10:52.564 --> 10:53.696
Oh, Pee-paw!

10:53.740 --> 10:55.698
-Use it in a sentence.
-Um...

10:55.742 --> 10:57.744
Hey, Pee-paw.

10:57.787 --> 11:00.268
[ Sighs ]

11:00.311 --> 11:01.356
Pee-paw it is.

11:01.399 --> 11:04.446
♪♪

11:05.055 --> 11:08.102
Penis-lavania.

11:08.145 --> 11:10.844
Remember that?
It's funny.

11:10.887 --> 11:13.542
Oh, damn it. It's stuck.What's stuck?

11:13.585 --> 11:15.370
-Floss is stuck.
-Just pull it out.

11:15.413 --> 11:16.676
I am.
I'm trying to pull it out.

11:16.719 --> 11:18.373
-Pull harder.
-I'm pulling harder.

11:18.416 --> 11:20.201
I can't get it out, man.
-Yank it.

11:20.244 --> 11:21.637
Babe, I don't like
the way this feels.

11:21.681 --> 11:22.986
I really --
-Pull, pull, pull.

11:23.030 --> 11:24.814
Can you get something
to cut it out?

11:24.858 --> 11:26.729
What do you want me
to cut it with?Oh, this does not feel good.

11:26.773 --> 11:28.600
Jesus. Can you bite it out
or something?

11:28.644 --> 11:29.863
Why would I
bite it out?

11:29.906 --> 11:31.125
Because I need it
out of my mouth.

11:31.168 --> 11:32.474
Just get it out.

11:32.517 --> 11:33.910
You want me to bite it
out of your face?

11:33.954 --> 11:35.216
-Yes, bite it out of my face.
-Oh, my God.

11:35.259 --> 11:36.739
Do something,
because I can't handle this.

11:36.783 --> 11:38.045
Oh, my God. I can't believe
you're making me do this.

11:38.088 --> 11:39.611
Just look at the road.

11:39.655 --> 11:40.917
-I'm looking at the road.
-Calm down! God.

11:40.961 --> 11:42.266
I just -- I can't.
This hurts so bad.

11:42.310 --> 11:43.659
Here, here.
Is this better? Hmm? Hmm?

11:43.703 --> 11:45.313
Oh, God.
Oh, God, I can't see anything.

11:45.356 --> 11:46.314
Is that better?

11:46.357 --> 11:47.924
-There.
-Oh, my God!

11:47.968 --> 11:50.710
God.
Oh, my God,
that feels so much better.

11:51.493 --> 11:53.277
Whew.

11:53.321 --> 11:54.409
Oh, God.

11:54.452 --> 11:55.932
Are you
having an orgasm?

11:55.976 --> 11:57.847
No. This feels so much better
than an orgasm.

11:59.109 --> 12:01.372
So,
tell me about yourselves.

12:02.809 --> 12:04.941
As people.

12:04.985 --> 12:06.160
You got a girlfriend?

12:06.203 --> 12:07.378
She doesn't like to be
called that,

12:07.422 --> 12:08.902
but we're moving
pretty fast.

12:08.945 --> 12:11.774
We don't like labels.
-I'm in love.

12:11.818 --> 12:15.778
He's over 2,000 years old,
has long hair, and a beard.

12:16.431 --> 12:17.998
He's a constant
in my life.

12:18.041 --> 12:19.782
[ Sighs ]

12:19.826 --> 12:21.262
You don't want
to know his name?

12:21.305 --> 12:23.003
I just assumed
he was fake.

12:23.046 --> 12:25.483
It's Jesus.
I'm in love with Jesus.

12:25.527 --> 12:27.311
Oh. So I was right.

12:27.355 --> 12:30.401
♪♪

12:31.881 --> 12:33.448
[ Inhales deeply ]

12:33.491 --> 12:35.232
How long
have I been asleep?

12:35.276 --> 12:36.494
What?
Ooh.

12:36.538 --> 12:38.409
-You were driving.
-Yeah, but --

12:38.453 --> 12:40.934
A couple highway markers,
tops. Right?

12:40.977 --> 12:42.718
You mean mile markers?

12:42.762 --> 12:44.285
What was the last one
you saw?

12:44.328 --> 12:46.330
17, I think?

12:46.896 --> 12:49.246
You've been asleep
for three miles?

12:49.290 --> 12:50.682
Okay, okay.
But that's --

12:50.726 --> 12:52.293
But that's only two and half
minutes at this sp--

12:52.336 --> 12:53.555
You were supposed
to keep me awake!

12:53.598 --> 12:55.992
Don't slap me.
It's not my fault.

12:56.036 --> 12:57.951
God.
Pull over. Let me drive.

12:57.994 --> 12:59.779
No. You are
in no condition to drive.

12:59.822 --> 13:02.259
I'm -- You're right.

13:02.303 --> 13:04.044
-Hey. Hit me.
-What?

13:04.087 --> 13:05.872
-Hit me in the face.
-Why would I do that?

13:05.915 --> 13:08.396
-To keep me awake.
-I would knock you out.

